1 About
*******

‘bib’ is a small Emacs package for quickly retrieving bibliographic
metadata for books, academic papers, and films.  Given only a title (and
optionally an author), it searches the relevant public APIs--Crossref,
ISBNdb, OMDb, TMDb, Letterboxd--locates the correct unique identifier
(DOI, ISBN, IMDb ID, or Letterboxd slug), and returns a ready-to-use
result: a DOI string, an IMDb URL, a Letterboxd slug, or a full BibTeX
entry (via zotra (https://github.com/mpedramfar/zotra)).

   This is not a full-featured reference manager--just a personal tool
that I decided to publish because others might find it useful.

   The development repository is on GitHub
(https://github.com/benthamite/bib).


