5.1 API keys
============

Several commands require API keys for the services they query.  Set
these variables in your init file or via ‘M-x customize-group RET bib
RET’:

Variable           Service   Required by                          How to get a key
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘bib-isbndb-key’   ISBNdb    ‘bib-search-isbn’                    isbndb.com (https://isbndb.com/isbn-database)
‘bib-omdb-key’     OMDb      ‘bib-search-imdb’                    omdbapi.com (https://www.omdbapi.com/)
‘bib-tmdb-key’     TMDb      ‘bib-translate-title-into-english’   themoviedb.org (https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api)

   If a key is empty or nil when the corresponding command is invoked, a
descriptive error message is shown.

   Example:

     (setopt bib-isbndb-key "your-isbndb-key-here")
     (setopt bib-omdb-key   "your-omdb-key-here")
     (setopt bib-tmdb-key   "your-tmdb-key-here")


File: bib.info,  Node: General options,  Prev: API keys,  Up: Configuration

5.2 General options
===================

Variable                      Type      Default               Description
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘bib-letterboxd-use-slug-p’   boolean   ‘nil’                 When non-nil, ‘bib-search-letterboxd’ returns the slug by default; when nil, the full URL.  A prefix argument inverts the behavior for a single invocation.
‘bib-letterboxd-user-agent’   string    ‘"Mozilla/5.0 ..."’   User-Agent header sent when querying Letterboxd

   Example:

     ;; prefer Letterboxd slugs instead of full URLs
     (setopt bib-letterboxd-use-slug-p t)


